
[1]passover

   P`ASSOVER, n. [pass and over.] A feast of the Jews, instituted to
   commemorate the providential escape of the Hebrews, in Egypt, when God
   smiting the first-born of the Egyptians, passed over the houses of the
   Israelites, which were marked with the blood of the paschal lamb.

   1. The sacrifice offered at the feast of the passover.
